            <guid>http://chicago.pm.org/blog/2016/04/30/blog-cpantesters-at-the-perl-qa-hackathon/</guid>
            <description><![CDATA[
                <p><a href="http://preaction.me">Doug Bell</a>, the new leader of <a href="http://cpantesters.org">the CPANTesters
project</a>, blogged about his accomplishments at
<a href="http://act.qa-hackathon.org/qa2016/">this year&#39;s Perl QA Hackathon</a>,
including tracking <a href="http://github.com/cpan-testers/cpantesters-project">the CPANTesters project
goals</a> and starting
<a href="http://github.com/cpan-testers/cpantesters-deploy">an automated deploy for
CPANTesters</a> using
<a href="http://rexify.org">Rex, a Perl-based devops tool</a>.</p>

<p>Read Doug&#39;s post on his website:
<a href="http://preaction.me/blog/2016/04/30/perl-qa-hackathon-cpantesters/">http://preaction.me/blog/2016/04/30/perl-qa-hackathon-cpantesters/</a></p>

